cleaned_desc: 生活对账 in English 中美生活对账可以用Cost of living comparison between China and the US来表达也可以说Living cost comparison between China and the United States 例句 Recently a wave of cost of living comparison between China and the US has emerged on Xiaohongshu attracting the attention of netizens on both sides of the Pacific最近小红书上掀起了一股中美生活成本对账的热潮吸引了太平洋两岸网友的关注 The living cost comparison between China and the United States reveals some differences in daily expenses中美生活成本的对账揭示了日常开销方面一些差异 对账相关扩充 reconcile accounts侧重使账目收支等达成一致在财务领域常用较为专业 例句The finance department is busy reconciling accounts at the end of the fiscal year财政部门在财政年度结束时忙着对账 check accounts强调检查账户的动作以保证账户信息准确 例句We should regularly check accounts to avoid financial mistakes我们应该定期对账以避免财务错误 balance accounts常用于商业和会计领域指核对和调整账户余额使其达到一致 例句The accountant has to balance accounts every month to ensure the financial statements are accurate会计每个月都要对账以确保财务报表的准确性 对账相关词汇 accountant名词意为会计人员会计师对账是他们的重要工作之一 例句The accountant is responsible for reconciling accounts and preparing financial reports这位会计师负责对账和编制财务报告 ledger名词指分类账对账时需要核对分类账上的各项记录 例句The data in the ledger is the basis for reconciling accounts分类账中的数据是对账的基础 discrepancy名词意为差异不符对账的目的之一就是发现账目中的差异 例句After reconciling accounts they found some discrepancies in the income records对账后他们发现收入记录中有一些差异

cleaned_desc: 我有一个问题不知当讲不当讲 I have a question I dont know if to say it or not 在小红书上观察了这么多天看了很多对账的贴子或者美国人自己发的贴子 有的人一天打几份工有的人交的税超过工资都百分之五十有的人房租甚至超过工资的三分之一还有些数不胜数 如果这是假的那当然最好毕竟对岸的人民有一个好生活但是这如果是真的为什么没有人去尝试改变一下 甚至于看起来没有人同情别人的遭遇或者说美国的教育体系是将人教导成一个自私的人吗 以上就是我的疑问如果有冒犯到的地方请您原谅或者私信我我会向您道歉 I have observed many days on the Little Red Book and read many reconciliation posts even those posted by Americans themselves Some people work several jobs a day some pay taxes that exceed their wages by 50 some rent even exceeds onethird of their wages and there are countless others If this is fake then of course its best after all the people on the other side have a good life But if this is true why hasnt anyone tried to change it Even it seems that no one sympathizes with the plight of others Or is the education system in the United States teaching people to be selfish The above is my question If you have offended me in any way please forgive me or message me directly and I will apologize to you The above is from Internet translation

cleaned_title: 我是TikTok难民吗Am I a TikTok refuge
cleaned_desc: Deepseek translation 简短回答是我并不是跟风加入的虽然我是在TikTok用户大迁徙浪潮期间来到小红书的但这更多是长期好奇的累积结果早前许多中国朋友就不断安利这个平台只是我以前实在提不起兴趣 其实我连TikTok账号都没有尽管印尼是全球TikTok用户最多的国家我爸妈甚至都玩TikTok唯独我不碰这些但现在入驻小红书后我却彻底沉迷了首先是清爽的体验没有每隔几分钟就被广告轰炸的窒息感其次是精准的内容推送能让我专注探索特定领域的优质内容至于和网友的互动其实我一直与祖国同胞保持联系深知他们的热情友善补充说明一下2000年代中期到2010年代我曾从事中国进口贸易频繁往返中国十余次亲眼见证了这片土地日新月异的发展 总之我选择在这里扎根既是为了贴近血脉里的中国情怀也是期待结识志同道合的朋友或许还能在这个充满活力的社区里收获新知 The short answer is I am not Although I joined during the TikTok refuges rush it was more of cumulation of curiosity and Chinese friends who were urging me to join before but I had no interest I have no Tiktok to start with although Indonesia has the most Tiktok users in the world My mom and dad even have it but I dont But now that I am on Xiaohongshu I am addicted to it first of all its so refreshing that I dont get bombarded by advertisement every a couple of minutes and secondly the content are more targeted to what I like and seems like I can be focused on a certain niche of contents As for the interaction with the people I have always been in contact with people from motherland anyway so I know how nice and welcoming they are For context I used to do import business from China in mid 2000s to mid 2010s so I have gone back and forth to China many times and saw the growth with my own eyes Anyway I am here to stay stay close to my Chinese roots make some friends and probably learn a thing or two here

cleaned_desc: You are new here but you are not a nuisance When its come to the TikTok refugee I have a lot of things to share Firstly althoughIts my first time that ive heard the term TikTok refugee recently I dont feel any dislike or aversion to it At first i dont know the true meaning of the TikTok refugee After understanding it i find it quite interesting TikTok refugee means the former TikTok users who can no longer use the tiktok due to a ban come to xhs to seek a new outlet for comfort I think as for most existing XiaoHongShu users they would be very welcome to communicate with tiktok refugee because people here are very nice Secondly I had seen some Tiktok refugees posted to ask some questions like do Chinese people regard tiktok refugees on Xhs as invaders what do you think of the influx of tiktok refugees Or are Chinese netizens annoyed at all people comming to this App I totally understamd your concerns No I dont think they are invaders They are just users who want to share and communicate just like anyone else on the platform It helps to create a more diverse and interesting community Besides Xiaohongshu is an app for sharing and conversation and having foreigners here can be enriching and diverse Besidesthe users here might be quite supportive and willing to see amazing crossovers among different cultures At last I found it interesting that many new users start with thier cute pets I hope everyone here have a nice experience Please remember that You are new here but you are not a nuisanceTiktok refugee refugee

cleaned_title: You too can learn Chinese Pt 5 final
cleaned_desc: This is my final video in this series Its relevant to note that since beginning to learn Chinese I have been fascinated with the written language For me I believe that the value of learning the characters has been in learning a totally new way to me of processing the world However in the last couple of days one of my new Chinese friends has demonstrated effectively that it is possible to communicate in pinyin even without the tones So perhaps if youre focusing on speaking you may be able to manage without the characters I hope youve found this series useful and its helped you believe that you too can learn Chinese Next Ill be sharing a Chinese adventure story that I think people in the West really need to know 非常感谢您对本系列的评论和留言我学到了很多东西希望我们能鼓励一群新人学习中文下一个系列在我完全专注于文化之前将讲述永乐皇帝和中国航海探险
combined_text: You too can learn Chinese Pt 5 final. This is my final video in this series Its relevant to note that since beginning to learn Chinese I have been fascinated with the written language For me I believe that the value of learning the characters has been in learning a totally new way to me of processing the world However in the last couple of days one of my new Chinese friends has demonstrated effectively that it is possible to communicate in pinyin even without the tones So perhaps if youre focusing on speaking you may be able to manage without the characters I hope youve found this series useful and its helped you believe that you too can learn Chinese Next Ill be sharing a Chinese adventure story that I think people in the West really need to know 非常感谢您对本系列的评论和留言我学到了很多东西希望我们能鼓励一群新人学习中文下一个系列在我完全专注于文化之前将讲述永乐皇帝和中国航海探险

cleaned_desc: Tiktok Refugees把红薯的琉量全部搅匀了好多以前没见过的高质量原住民笔记推到我主页猛猛关注几十个西餐给我吃爽了文化美食艺术音乐手工运动有高中生有常青藤教授有奶奶爷爷有开飞机的有掏烟囱的有帅哥美女 各种国内外平民对账像更像是解密游戏魔法对冲还看到了很多纯真善良的小老外感动得哭唧唧 我相信不论是我们这边还是他们那边一定有人通过这次的事件看到听到感受到冥冥中拨动了命运的齿轮百年未有之大变局 也许过不久他们就会回家但朋友见面玩得开心就好了不用永远住一起那些见面时候产生美好回忆会永远留在心里 Ive been surfing the Internet intensively these two days Its incredibly refreshing to immerse myself in secretly learning English The TikTok Refugees have stirred up the traffic on Xiaohongshu A lot of highquality notes from local users that Ive never seen before have been pushed to my homepage And they also brought their good contents about culture cuisine art music handicrafts and sports The people are sharing their lifes There are high school students Ivy League professors grandparents pilots chimney sweeps as well as handsome boys and beautiful girls The truth exchanges between domestic people and abroad are more like exciting detective games Ive also seen many innocent and kind hearted foreign friends who were so so touched by warmhearted comments a big part of users here are girls who are angels I believe that whether its on our side or theirs there must be people who through this event have seen heard and felt something that has subtly set the wheels of fate in motion The global village is connected to the Internet Something must have changed This is a great transformation unseen in a century Maybe theyll leave soon but its fine as long as friends have a good time when they meet Theres no need for them to stay together all the time Those wonderful memories created during the meeting will always remain in our hearts tiktokrefugee 抖音难民日记

cleaned_desc: Im a Puerto Rican American TikTok Refugee I just want to say how proud I am of all of us for standing strong against the unfairness weve faced from our government Weve proven that TikTok wasnt just about videos but it was about people connections and a space where we could share and learn from each other no matter where were from Were not giving in and were not selling out Well keep sharing our stories and connecting across cultures Im here to connect with anyone who wants to chat share ideas or just vibe I understand there are limits to what we can talk about here and Ill do my best to be respectful of this platform the culture and everyone in it Lets keep creating sharing and lifting each other up Together were stronger than ever Thank you all youre amazing Im going to put a translation in the comments because I met my word limit

cleaned_title: 美国小姐姐教我什么是一线城市
cleaned_desc: 昨晚和一个可爱的美国小姐姐对账学了点新知识 她说请教一下我对你们的一线城市比较感兴趣但是搞不懂是什么意思一线城市到底指的是州还是市 我说简单讲中国的省差不多类似于你们美国的州中国的市和你们的市差不多中国的一线城市评价标准看人口和经济规模说的是中国最发达的几个城市和你们的纽约市差不多 结果美国小姐姐来了一句一线城市就是那种走夜路被人噶了的城市吗 三线城市就是指可以不需要丈夫陪伴就能晚上遛狗的城市吗 我一时语塞啊卧槽 Let me put it simply Chinas provinces are similar to your states in the United States and Chinas cities are similar to yours The evaluation criteria for firsttier cities in China based on population and economic scale are the most developed cities in China similar to your New York City As a result the American cute girl said Are firsttier cities the kind of cities where people walk at night and get caught Do thirdtier cities refer to cities where you can walk your dog at night without a husbands company I was speechless Ah shit 脑子转了一下才明白她在说地狱笑话她说在美国特大城市就等于治安最差的城市了类似于夜之城越是在纽约洛杉矶警察效率越差在小城市警察反而来的快一点 她还说在大城市的一些治安糟糕的街区如果你被人入室侵害了警察甚至不会来把你丢给入侵者直到天亮 She said that in the United States megacities are equivalent to the worst public security cities similar to night cities The more New York and Los Angeles the less efficient the police are while in smaller cities the police arrive faster She also said that in some of the worstpolice neighborhoods in big cities if you are invaded the police wont even come and leave you to the intruder until dawn 我查了一下美国最高法确实有一条判定 警察只有维护法律的责任并没有保护公民的义务比如你正面临生命威胁美国警察可以选择救也可以选择不救救与不救由其自行决定 又给了我一点小小的夜之城震撼

cleaned_title: TikTok Refugees guide to China Apps
cleaned_desc: Dear Tiktok Refugees Since you are here on Redbook might as well explore other Chinese apps that are kind of similar to other American social media platforms I had trouble registering some of them at first but eventually got the hang of it The trick is you should get Wchat first Once you are registered and verified by Wchat then itll be very easy to sign up to other apps since most of foreigners do not have a local Chinese cellphone number good luck and feel free to ask me questions
combined_text: TikTok Refugees guide to China Apps. Dear Tiktok Refugees Since you are here on Redbook might as well explore other Chinese apps that are kind of similar to other American social media platforms I had trouble registering some of them at first but eventually got the hang of it The trick is you should get Wchat first Once you are registered and verified by Wchat then itll be very easy to sign up to other apps since most of foreigners do not have a local Chinese cellphone number good luck and feel free to ask me questions

cleaned_desc: Hi here is Trend Panda Imagine you just saw the funniest meme ever In English you type LOL In China we say XS or XSWL But what do they really mean What Do XS XSWL Stand For Actually they are abbreviations of two Chinese phrases 1 XS xs 笑死 xiào sǐ Laugh to death literally Meaning Similar to LOL or LMAO in English Example xs这个梗图好搞笑 LOL this meme is too funny Note Since 死 sǐ means death in Chinese some people prefer using 笑鼠 xiào shǔ laugh mouse instead It sounds similar but feels friendlier But xs is totally okay 2 XSWL xswl 笑死我了 xiào sǐ wǒ le Im dying of laughter literally Meaning Even stronger than XS like Im crying laughing or ROFL Example xswl这个视频太有意思了 LMAO this video is so interesting When to Use Both XS and XSWL can be used when you find something funny Want a more formal way to say something is funny in Chinese Try these 好笑 hǎo xiào Funny 很好笑 好好笑 Really funny 有趣 yǒu qù Interesting 很有趣 好有意思 Very interesting Whats something that made you XS recently Tell us in Mandarin Whats the funniest meme youve seen recently Share it in the comments so we can all XSWL

cleaned_desc: @小红书创作助手 @小红书REDesign 感谢大家的分享让我有了新的认知有朋友提出超出50k的部分是40但因为基数有提高对于日常的影响相对小一点不在讨论范围我为什么更关注这个阶段换算一下 年入50k月入4100缴税7500月均625实入3475 年入40k月入3333缴税5500月均458实入2875 以上还不含保险房产税助学贷款等石化R石化R 虽然都在讨论免费的医疗或者相关福利待遇但这应该是属于额外缴纳的保险范围税收应该用于国家发展城市建设那大家对以上真的满意吗诚然国家发展和城市建设离不开税收但不应该在这个阶段加这么高的税四百或者六百对于这个阶段的生活是有很大帮助的基本的生活有了保障生活质量才会有幸福感吧吧唧R吧唧R吧唧R Thanks to everyones sharing I have a new understanding Some friends proposed that the tax paid for the part exceeding 50k is 40 but because the income base has increased the impact on daily life is relatively small and it is not within the scope of discussion Why do I pay more attention to this income stage A simple conversion Annual income of 50k monthly income of 4100 tax of 7500 monthly average of 625 actual income of 3475 Annual income of 40k monthly income of 3333 tax of 5500 monthly average of 458 actual income of 2875 The above does not include the insurance property tax student loans etc mentioned by everyone Although everyone is discussing free medical care or related welfare benefits this should be covered by additional insurance premiums Taxes should be used for the development of the country and the construction of cities Are people satisfied with the above While it is true that the development of the country and the building of cities cannot do without taxes it is not necessary to impose such high taxes at this income level More than 400 or 600 can make a big difference in the lives of people at this income level Once basic living needs are met people will feel a sense of wellbeing I hope it wont cause any trouble for you

cleaned_desc: Located in Beijing the Palace Museum Forbidden City has a long history It was constructed from 1406 to 1420 The name Forbidden City comes from the fact that it was the imperial palace where the emperor and his family lived and worked It was offlimits to ordinary people hence the term forbidden This grand complex is a masterpiece of ancient Chinese palace architecture with its magnificent halls exquisite decorations and symmetrical layout showcasing the supreme power and authority of the emperor in feudal society 紫禁城故宫博物院位于北京的中心始建于明成祖永乐年间1406年至1420年期间建成 紫禁城之名源于它是皇帝及其家人居住和办公的皇家宫殿普通百姓禁止进入因此得名禁城再加上其尊贵神圣的属性故称紫禁城 这座宏伟的建筑群是古代中国宫殿建筑的杰作其雄伟的大殿精美的装饰以及对称的布局彰显了封建社会中皇帝至高无上的权力与威严 @故宫文化
